In addition to the characters defining the
effusus
group, the species can be recognized by: (1) head entirely blue (often faded to greenish in collection specimens) ( Fig. 5 D–E); (2) pronotum yellow-brown, mesonotum blue-brown ( Fig. 5A ); (3) tegmina green with small yellow spots also beyond nodal line;

spots rounded and not coalescent (
Fig. 5A
); (4) tegmina without large pale yellow patch at nodal line and with apical margin slightly infuscate (
Fig. 5A
).

